    "title": "CPI Inflation Multipliers for Historical Dollar Conversion, 1920-1948 to 2024",
    "chapter": "08-the-salary-ledger",
    "license": "CC0 1.0",
    "last_updated": "2026-05-24",
    "base": "CPI-U, 1982-1984 = 100",
    "methodology_note": "CPI-U annual average index values from in2013dollars.com, cross-referenced against BLS historical tables. The 2024 annual average CPI-U is 313.69. Multipliers are calculated as 313.69 / historical_cpi. These multipliers convert historical dollars to 2024 purchasing power equivalents. Note: CPI is one of three inflator methods used in this chapter. Wage index and GDP share inflators produce different (generally larger) results."
  },
