  "inflator_comparison_note": "CPI measures consumer purchasing power and is the most conservative inflator. Wage index measures what the same labor would command today and produces roughly 1.5-2x larger figures. GDP share measures the relative share of economic output and produces roughly 3-4x larger figures than CPI. The chapter reports all three to show the methodological sensitivity."
